The paper is about image recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs), which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the limitations of the current CNN-based image recognition paradigm and proposes a new approach, which involves more advanced techniques such as LSTM and GRU, indicating a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques such as embedding, which is a subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL).
